title: KrakenR
text: KrakenR package provides user-friendly interface Kraken cryptocurrency exchange’s REST API. allows R users access real-time historical market data, asset information, exchange metrics, making valuable tool financial analysts, traders, researchers interested cryptocurrency markets. vignette introduce key functionalities package, showcasing use API functions retrieve market data .

title: KrakenR
text: can install KrakenR directly GitHub:
code: # Generate GitHub token usethis::create_github_token()  # Install KrakenR (replace XXXXXXXXXXX with the token generated) devtools::install_github(     repo = "ptds2024/group6-project",     build_vignettes = TRUE,     auth_token = "XXXXXXXXXXX",     dependencies = TRUE ) # Load the package library(KrakenR) #> Error in get(paste0(generic, ".", class), envir = get_method_env()) :  #>   object 'type_sum.accel' not found

title: KrakenR
text: package includes several key functions allow users fetch various types data Kraken exchange: getAssets() - Retrieve detailed asset information. getOB() - Fetch order book data specific trading pair. getOHLC() - Access OHLC (Open, High, Low, Close) data trading pair. getPairs() - Retrieve tradable asset pair information. getSpreads() - Fetch recent spread data. getStatus() - Get current system status Kraken exchange. getTickers() - Retrieve detailed ticker information trading pairs. getTime() - Fetch current Kraken server time. getTrades() - Retrieve recent trade data trading pair.

title: KrakenR
text: section provides detailed walkthrough using KrakenR access Kraken market data.

title: KrakenR
text: retrieve detailed information available assets specific ones: getAssets() function returns data frame containing asset information, asset class, decimals, status.
code: # Fetch all available assets assets_all <- getAssets()  # Fetch data for specific assets assets_specific <- getAssets(c("BTC", "ETH", "ADA"))

title: KrakenR
text: can use getOB() fetch order book data specific trading pair: output includes bid ask orders, sorted price, can used market analysis. Note NA values: NA values output normal result structure order book data. Bids asks presented separate rows, bid-related columns populated bid entries ask-related columns populated ask entries. NA values simply indicate data exists columns respective side order book.
code: # Fetch order book data for ADAEUR pair order_book <- getOB("ADAEUR")  # Fetch order book data with a limit on the number of orders order_book_limited <- getOB("ADAEUR", count = 3)

title: KrakenR
text: getOHLC() function allows retrieve OHLC (Open, High, Low, Close) data given trading pair various time intervals: function useful technical analysis charting.
code: # Fetch 1-minute interval OHLC data for ADAEUR ohlc_data <- getOHLC("ADAEUR", interval = 1)  # Fetch 4-hour interval data ohlc_data_4h <- getOHLC("ADAEUR", interval = 240)

title: KrakenR
text: retrieve tradable asset pairs details: can also filter specific details leverage, fees, margin.
code: # Fetch all available asset pairs pairs_all <- getPairs()  # Fetch information for a specific pair pair_info <- getPairs(c("ADAEUR", "BTCUSD"))

title: KrakenR
text: get recent spread data trading pair: spread data provides insight bid-ask spread time, useful liquidity analysis.
code: # Fetch spread data for ADAEUR spread_data <- getSpreads("ADAEUR")

title: KrakenR
text: fetch real-time ticker information trading pairs: function provides real-time price, volume, trading information.
code: # Fetch ticker information for all pairs tickers_all <- getTickers()  # Fetch ticker information for specific pairs tickers_specific <- getTickers(c("ADAEUR", "BTCUSD"))

title: KrakenR
text: retrieve recent trade data trading pair:
code: # Fetch recent trades for ADAEUR recent_trades <- getTrades("ADAEUR")  # Fetch trades since a specific timestamp recent_trades_since <- getTrades("ADAEUR", since = "2024-10-01 12:00:00")

title: KrakenR
text: check operational status Kraken exchange:
code: # Fetch both system status and timestamp status_info <- getStatus()  # Fetch only system status system_status <- getStatus("status") #> [1] "System Status: online"               "System Status: 2024-12-18T16:45:53Z"

title: KrakenR
text: can check current server time UNIX RFC formats:
code: # Fetch UNIX time server_time_unix <- getTime("unix")  # Fetch RFC 1123 time server_time_rfc <- getTime("rfc") #> [1] "UNIX Time: 2024-12-18 16:45:53"

title: Shiny-App
text: KrakenR Shiny app interactive application designed showcase functionality KrakenR package, providing users near real-time insights cryptocurrency markets. vignette walks user interface elements, underlying logic, challenges faced development, focus efficiency innovative solutions.

title: Shiny-App
text: app integrates live data Kraken’s API, presenting challenges API rate limits, data freshness, responsiveness. overcome challenges: Rate Limiting: custom rate_limited_call function implemented ensure API calls comply Kraken’s restrictions maintaining seamless updates. Reactive Caching: Data trading pairs tickers cached specific durations (e.g., 24 hours trading pairs, 5 seconds tickers) minimize redundant API calls. Granular Reactivity: Reactive values observers ensure relevant components updated data changes, reducing computational overhead.

title: Shiny-App
text: dashboard central hub app, providing overview selected trading pair’s key metrics visualizations.

title: Shiny-App
text: dropdown menu allows users select trading pair dynamically. dropdown options fetched getPairs API endpoint updated reactively. selected pair triggers updates components dashboard.

title: Shiny-App
text: header displays: Trading Pair Title: Reactively updates based selected pair. Last Price: latest ask price ticker data. custom reactive function determines box’s color, transitioning dynamically green (price increase), red (price decrease), gray (change). 24-Hour Change: Calculated OHLC data, showing percentage price change past 24 hours similar reactive color scheme. 24-Hour Volume: cumulative trading volume past 24 hours, displayed selected cryptocurrency symbol. Price Alert System: Allows users set alerts price goes specified value, keeping updated real time.

previous_headings: User Interface Elements > Dashboard > Main Information Header
title: Shiny-App
text: implement dynamic colors: helper function, get_color, evaluates current previous values. Colors updated reactively using renderValueBox, ensuring real-time feedback market trends.

title: Shiny-App
text: market chart visualizes selected trading pair’s price data, offering multiple chart types statistical overlays.

title: Shiny-App
text: Users can choose candlestick, line, area charts. plotly package ensures interactivity high-quality rendering.

title: Shiny-App
text: Options include: Moving Average: smoothed price trend using rolling mean. Bollinger Bands: Visualizes volatility potential price trends. Exponential Moving Average (EMA): Highlights recent price changes sensitively simple moving average. overlay data computed reactively added chart, ensuring updates occur seamlessly without reloading entire component.

title: Shiny-App
text: One challenging components, bid/ask table dynamically visualizes order book grouped data bar plot background.

title: Shiny-App
text: Price intervals calculated dynamically using get_scaled_intervals function, adjusts based median price order book ensure clarity regardless trading pair’s price range.

what: HTML Table with Bar Plot Background
title: Shiny-App
text: create bar plot effect: row’s background width proportional cumulative quantity. Custom HTML inline CSS dynamically adjust background size color row. Data grouped aggregated optimize rendering performance. feature required careful handling CSS styling reactive updates ensure synchronization real-time data changes.

title: Shiny-App
text: last trades table provides snapshot recent transactions, including: Price Volume Order Type (buy/sell) Execution Type (market/limit)

previous_headings: User Interface Elements > Last Trades Table
title: Shiny-App
text: Users can filter trades order execution types. table updates reactively upon user interaction manual refresh, ensuring displayed data always relevant.

title: Shiny-App
text: news tab integrates CryptoPanic API provide latest cryptocurrency news.

title: Shiny-App
text: Dynamic News Cards: Articles displayed interactive cards publication date, title, currency relevance. Pagination: Users can navigate news articles using custom pagination controls. Modal View: Clicking news card opens modal displaying article iframe. fallback link ensures accessibility iframe fails load.

title: Shiny-App
text: News data fetched periodically deduplicated using dplyr, ensuring new unique articles displayed. Reactive pagination adjusts dynamically based total number articles selected page.

title: Shiny-App
text: app integrates AI-powered GPT model answer user questions cryptocurrency assets. Users can interact model typing queries chat interface.

title: Shiny-App
text: Provides information cryptocurrency assets. Ensures responses generated dynamically using external AI backend hosted Render. Allows users ask open-ended questions, enhancing app’s analytical capabilities. Note: backend powering AI model separate package documents hosted available repository within render-backend folder.

title: Shiny-App
text: KrakenR Shiny app demonstrates advanced R Shiny techniques, integrating real-time data, interactive visualizations, AI-powered analytics. Key innovations include: Dynamic adaptive visualizations (e.g., bid/ask table bar plot backgrounds). Efficient data management strategies handle near real-time updates. polished UI design enhances usability aesthetics. Price Alert System notify users prices go specific threshold. AI Chat Assistant integration, enabling users ask questions receive insights cryptocurrency assets. addressing complex challenges ensuring computational efficiency, app serves robust platform cryptocurrency market analysis.

what: Retrieve Order Book Data from Kraken Exchange — getOB
title: Retrieve Order Book Data from Kraken Exchange — getOB
text: function fetches order book data Kraken API specified trading pair.

title: Retrieve Order Book Data from Kraken Exchange — getOB
code: getOB(pair, count = NULL)

title: Retrieve Order Book Data from Kraken Exchange — getOB
text: pair character string specifying trading pair (e.g., "ADAEUR"). required parameter. count optional integer 1 500 specifying number orders retrieve. Default NULL.

title: Retrieve Order Book Data from Kraken Exchange — getOB
text: data frame containing order book data requested trading pair, bid orders appearing first (sorted price ascending) followed ask orders (sorted price ascending).

title: Retrieve Order Book Data from Kraken Exchange — getOB

what: Retrieve OHLC Data from Kraken Exchange — getOHLC
title: Retrieve OHLC Data from Kraken Exchange — getOHLC
text: function fetches OHLC (Open, High, Low, Close) data Kraken API specified trading pair.

title: Retrieve OHLC Data from Kraken Exchange — getOHLC
code: getOHLC(pair, interval = 1, since = NULL)

title: Retrieve OHLC Data from Kraken Exchange — getOHLC
text: pair character string specifying trading pair (e.g., "ADAEUR"). required parameter. interval time frame interval minutes user-friendly format (e.g., "1h" 1 hour, "1d" 1 day, etc.). Possible values "1m", "5m", "15m", "30m", "1h", "4h", "1d", "1w", "2w", numeric values minutes. Default 1 minute. since character string human-readable date-time (e.g., "2024-10-01 12:00:00") Unix timestamp. Default NULL (returns available data).

title: Retrieve OHLC Data from Kraken Exchange — getOHLC
text: data frame containing OHLC data requested trading pair.

title: Retrieve OHLC Data from Kraken Exchange — getOHLC

what: Retrieve Tradable Asset Pairs Information from Kraken Exchange — getPairs
title: Retrieve Tradable Asset Pairs Information from Kraken Exchange — getPairs
text: function fetches detailed information tradable asset pairs Kraken API, either pairs specified subset.

title: Retrieve Tradable Asset Pairs Information from Kraken Exchange — getPairs
code: getPairs(pairs = "All", info = "info", country_code = NULL)

title: Retrieve Tradable Asset Pairs Information from Kraken Exchange — getPairs
text: pairs character vector specifying pairs retrieve. Use "" fetch data pairs. specific pairs, provide abbreviations (e.g., "ADAEUR" c("ADAEUR", "BTCUSD")). Default "". info character vector specify level detail ("info", "leverage", "fees", "margin"). Default "info". country_code single character string specifying country code filter pairs. Use NULL needed. Default NULL.

title: Retrieve Tradable Asset Pairs Information from Kraken Exchange — getPairs
text: data frame containing detailed information requested asset pairs nested lists columns multiple values.

what: Retrieve Recent Spreads Data from Kraken Exchange — getSpreads
title: Retrieve Recent Spreads Data from Kraken Exchange — getSpreads
text: function fetches recent spread data Kraken API specified trading pair.

title: Retrieve Recent Spreads Data from Kraken Exchange — getSpreads
code: getSpreads(pair, since = NULL, timestamp = FALSE)

title: Retrieve Recent Spreads Data from Kraken Exchange — getSpreads
text: pair character string specifying trading pair (e.g., "XTZUSD", "ADAEUR"). required parameter. since character string human-readable date-time (e.g., "2024-10-01 12:00:00") Unix timestamp. Default NULL. timestamp logical value. TRUE, function returns spreads data frame last timestamp future polling. FALSE (default), returns data frame.

title: Retrieve Recent Spreads Data from Kraken Exchange — getSpreads
text: data frame containing spread data list containing data frame last timestamp.

title: Retrieve Recent Spreads Data from Kraken Exchange — getSpreads

title: Retrieve the Current Kraken Server Time — getTime
text: format character string specifying time format return. Use "unix" UNIX timestamp "rfc" RFC 1123 format. default "unix".

title: Retrieve the Current Kraken Server Time — getTime
text: POSIXct object format = "unix" character string RFC 1123 format format = "rfc".

what: Retrieve Recent Trades Data from Kraken Exchange — getTrades
title: Retrieve Recent Trades Data from Kraken Exchange — getTrades
text: function fetches recent trade data Kraken API specified trading pair.

title: Retrieve Recent Trades Data from Kraken Exchange — getTrades
code: getTrades(pair, since = NULL, count = NULL)

title: Retrieve Recent Trades Data from Kraken Exchange — getTrades
text: pair character string specifying trading pair (e.g., "XTZUSD", "ADAEUR"). required parameter. since character string human-readable date-time (e.g., "2024-10-01 12:00:00") Unix timestamp. Default NULL (returns available trades). count optional integer 1 1000 specifying number trades retrieve. Default NULL (returns 1000 trades).

title: Retrieve Recent Trades Data from Kraken Exchange — getTrades
text: data frame containing recent trade data requested trading pair.

title: Retrieve Recent Trades Data from Kraken Exchange — getTrades
